SIMPLE: minutely
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Minutely
<hw>Mi*nute"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From 4th
<er>Minute</er>.]</ety> <def>In a minute manner; with minuteness;
exactly; nicely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minutely</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Minutely
<hw>Min"ute*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From 1st
<er>Minute</er>.]</ety> <def>Happening every minute; continuing;
unceasing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Throwing themselves absolutely upon God's <qex>minutely</qex>
providence.</q> <rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minutely</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Minutely
<hw>Min"ute*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>At intervals of a minute; very
often and regularly.</def> <rj><au>J. Philips.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Minutely</qex> proclaimed in thunder from heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minuteman</ent>⟦br⟧
